cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper proposes a deep neural network-based approach for indoor localization using Wi-Fi fingerprinting. This falls under the intersection of several sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of deep neural networks for classification and regression tasks, as well as the focus on indoor localization, makes cs.LG and cs.NI the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of computer vision techniques and the potential for control systems applications also make cs.CV and cs.SY possible sub-categories.
